sub_title: Assistant Legal Counsel (International Arbitration) at Permanent Court of Arbitration | LL.M. (Duke Law'21)
summary:
As Assistant Legal Counsel at the Permanent Court of Arbitration in the Netherlands, I have gained experience in administering complex international commercial and investment arbitration matters.

Previous experience includes advising local and international clients on corporate transactions, corporate governance, and compliance matters.

In 2015, I founded a nationwide nonprofit organization that provides free legal assistance to indigent clients—the first of its kind in Saudi Arabia. The nonprofit works collaboratively with lawyers throughout the country on family and labor matters and campaigns impacting more than 15,000 people.

As an individual, I am a dynamic go-getter who is rarely seen without a smile. Strong legal professional with a first-class LLB and an LL.M. from Duke University School of Law.
